description.narrative: National and provincial health authorities in selected provinces have improved capacity to plan, implement, monitor and report the delivery of gender-responsive MNCAH services, focused on the most disadvantaged, to prevent excess morbidity and mortality among girls, boys and women, including in humanitarian situations., which contributes to Child Health, Children With Disabilities, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Supply And Logistics, Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Communities, parents, caregivers and children have increased awareness of the consequences of violence and have the skills to protect children and women.
